strtools.py
Go to the documentation of this file.
1 #!/usr/bin/env python3
2 # -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
3 # vim:fileencoding=utf-8
4 """@brief Functions for various string and character manipulations
5 @file strtools.py
6 @package pybooster.strtools
7 @author Devyn Collier Johnson <DevynCJohnson@Gmail.com>
8 @copyright LGPLv3
9 @version 2016.03.20
10 
11 @section DESCRIPTION
12 This library contains
13  - Constants for various characters and character ranges
14  - Functions for various string and character manipulations
15  - Ascii, Hex (\\x*), UTF-8 (\\u*), UTF-16BE/UTF-32 (\\U*), HTML-Entities (&#*;)
16 
17 C-escapes = JS-escapes = HTML-named-ref = decimal ncr = hex ncr\n
18 '\\U0001d4c3' = '\\ud835\\udcc3' = &nscr; = &#120003; = &#x1D4C3;\n
19 '\\U0001d4a9' = '\\ud835\\udca9' = &Nscr; = &#119977; = &#x1D4A9;\n
20 
21 unicode+hex = 0x notation = css = utf16 = utf8 = uri%\n
22 U+1D4C3 = 0x1D4C3 = \01D4C3 = D835 DCC3 = F0 9D 93 83 = %F0%9D%93%83\n
23 U+1D4A9 = 0x1D4A9 = \01D4A9 = D835 DCA9 = F0 9D 92 A9 = %F0%9D%92%A9\n
24 
25 @section VARIABLES
26  - _refnum: stores an HTML reference number as a string (&#38;)
27  - _refname: stores an HTML name entity as a string (&amp;)
28  - _name: stores an unicode character name
29  - _char: stores a single character or an escape sequence (\\x26)
30  - _str: stores a string/text
31  - _int: stores an integer
32  - _hex: stores a hex sequence as an integer, str, or escape sequence
33  - _oct: stores an octal sequence as an integer, str, or escape sequence
34  - _bin: stores a binary sequence as an integer, str, or escape sequence
35  - _bytes: stores a bytes-type object
36  - _dict: specify a dictionary
37  - _search: a value to find
38  - _assert: indicate that some condition be met
39  - _numbase: specify the base of the number ('2'=binary; '16'=hex; etc.)
40  - _escape: boolean; "True" (the default) makes a function escape the output
41  - _endian: specify endian (little/big); default is the native value
42  - _encoding: specify encoding; the default value is "utf8"
43

365 INCOMPLETE_REF = re.compile('&[#]?[0-9A-Za-z]+')
366 ENTITY_REF = re.compile('&[0-9A-Za-z]+;')
367 CHAR_REF = re.compile('&#(?:[0-9]+|[Xx][0-9A-Fa-f]+);')
368 CHAR_REF2 = re.compile(
369  r'&(#[0-9]+;?'
370  r'|#[xX][0-9a-fA-F]+;?'
371  r'|[^\t\n\f <&#;]{1,32};?)'
372 )
373 LEADING_SURROGATE = re.compile(r'[\ud800-\udbff]')
374 TRAILING_SURROGATE = re.compile(r'[\udc00-\udfff]')

538 """
539 The values in CODES includes the HTML entity names and numbers.
540 The characters used as keys are encoded in UTF8 (\\u) or UTF-16BE (\\U).
541 
542 HTML5_REF maps the names of HTML5 character references to characters.
543 
544 NAME2INT maps character names to hexadecimal integers.
545 
546 INVALID_CHARREFS maps hexadecimal integers to characters that should not be used in HTML5.
547 """

5239 # STRING MANIPULATIONS
5240 
5241 
5242 def endletters(_str: str) -> str:
5243  """Keep the first and last letter of a single word
5244 
5245  >>> endletters('Test')
5246  'Tt'
5247  """
5248  return _str[:1] + _str[-1:]
5249 
5250 
5251 def firstletters(_str: str) -> str:
5252  """Remove the last letter of a single word
5253 
5254  >>> firstletters('Test')
5255  'Tes'
5256  """
5257  return _str[:-1]
5258 
5259 
5260 def lastletters(_str: str) -> str:
5261  """Remove the first letter of a single word
5262 
5263  >>> lastletters('Test')
5264  'est'
5265  """
5266  return _str[1:]
5267 
5268 
5269 def middleletters(_str: str) -> str:
5270  """Remove the first and last letter of a single word
5271 
5272  >>> middleletters('Test')
5273  'es'
5274  """
5275  return _str[1:-1]
5276 
5277 
5278 def insert_character(_str: str, _char: str, index: int) -> str:
5279  """Insert a character at the specified point of a string"""
5280  return _str[:index] + _char + _str[index:]
5281 
5282 
5283 def num2ordinal(_str: str) -> str:
5284  """Convert numbers to ordinals
5285 
5286  >>> num2ordinal('21')
5287  'twenty-first'
5288  """
5289  for _key in NUMBER_LIST:
5290  if _str == _key:
5291  _str = _str.lower().replace(_key, NUMBER_LIST[_key])
5292  return _str
5293 
5294 
5295 def ordinal2num(_str: str) -> str:
5296  """Convert ordinals to numbers
5297 
5298  >>> ordinal2num('twenty-first')
5299  '21'
5300  """
5301  for _key in ORDINAL_LIST:
5302  if _str == _key:
5303  _str = _str.lower().replace(_key, ORDINAL_LIST[_key])
5304  return _str
5305 
5306 
5307 def cap(_str: str) -> str:
5308  """Capitalize the beginning of each word
5309 
5310  >>> cap('this is a test.')
5311  'This Is A Test.'
5312  """
5313  return _str.title()
5314 
5315 
5316 def formal(_str: str) -> str:
5317  """Change the capitalization to the format used in titles
5318 
5319  >>> formal('this is a test.')
5320  'This Is A Test.'
5321  """
5322  return _str.title()
5323 
5324 
5325 def lowercase(_str: str) -> str:
5326  """Turn a string in lowercase
5327 
5328  >>> lowercase('THIS IS A TEST.')
5329  'this is a test.'
5330  """
5331  return _str.lower()
5332 
5333 
5334 def sentence(_str: str) -> str:
5335  """Capitalization the beginning of each sentence
5336 
5337  >>> sentence('this IS A TEST.')
5338  'This is a test.'
5339  """
5340  return _str.capitalize()
5341 
5342 
5343 def togglecase(_str: str) -> str:
5344  """Convert uppercase to lowercase and vice versa
5345 
5346  >>> togglecase('this IS A TEST.')
5347  'THIS is a test.'
5348  """
5349  return _str.swapcase()
5350 
5351 
5352 def uppercase(_str: str) -> str:
5353  """Turn a string in all caps
5354 
5355  >>> uppercase('this is a test.')
5356  'THIS IS A TEST.'
5357  """
5358  return _str.upper()
5359 
5360 
5361 def explode(_str: str) -> str:
5362  """Insert a space between each character
5363 
5364  >>> explode('this is a test.')
5365  ' t h i s i s a t e s t . '
5366  """
5367  return re.sub('(.?)', r' \1 ', _str).replace(r' ', r' ')
5368 
5369 
5370 def implode(_str: str) -> str:
5371  """Remove a space from between each character
5372 
5373  >>> implode('this is a test.')
5374  'thisisatest.'
5375  >>> implode(' t h i s i s a t e s t . ')
5376  'this is a test.'
5377  """
5378  return re.sub('(.?) (.?)', r'\1\2', _str).replace(r' ', r' ')
5379 
5380 
5381 def rmcurlycommas(_str: str) -> str:
5382  """Remove curly commas (፣ ، 、 ، ◌̦ ︐ ︑ ꛵ ᠂ ‍̓ )
5383 
5384  >>> rmcurlycommas('This is، a test.')
5385  'This is a test.'
5386  """
5387  return _str.replace(r'،', r'').replace(r'、', r'').replace(r'،', r'').replace(r'◌̦', r'').replace(r'︐', r'').replace(r'︑', r'').replace(r'᠂', r'').replace(r'‍̓', r'').replace(r'‍፣', r'').replace(r'‍꛵', r'')
5388 
5389 
5390 def replacecurlycommas(_str: str) -> str:
5391  """Replace curly commas with a regular comma (፣ ، 、 ، ◌̦ ︐ ︑ ꛵ ᠂ ‍̓ )
5392 
5393  >>> replacecurlycommas('This is، a test.')
5394  'This is, a test.'
5395  """

5457 def sqlstr(_obj, _strength: int=0) -> str:
5458  """Convert an object to a string and format the string to protect against SQL-Injection Attacks
5459 
5460  _strength indicates what characters should be removed or escaped
5461  0 = (Default) Remove curly quotes, commas, and brackets; escape quotes, slashes, and dashes
5462  1 = Same as 0, but removes characters instead of escaping
5463  2 = Same as 1, but remove additional characters such as .?!#;&%^:
5464  3 = Only keep ASCII letters and space
5465  """
5466  _obj = str(_obj)
5467  if _strength >= 3: # Only keep ASCII letters and space
5468  _out = r''
5469  for i in _obj:
5470  if i.isalpha() or i is r' ':
5471  _out += i
5472  return _out
5473  _obj = _obj.replace(r'{', r'').replace(r'}', r'').replace('\\', r'')
5474  _obj = _obj.replace(r'“', r'').replace(r'”', r'').replace(r'‘', r'').replace(r'’', r'').replace(r'、', r'').replace(r'،', r'') # Curly Quotes and Commas
5475  if not _strength: # _strength == 0
5476  return _obj.replace(r'"', r'&quot;').replace('\'', r'&#39;').replace(r'`', r'&#96;').replace(r'--', r'-')
5477  else: # _strength >= 1
5478  _obj = _obj.replace(r'"', r'').replace('\'', r'').replace(r'`', r'').replace(r'-', r'')
5479  if _strength >= 2:
5480  return _obj.replace(r'%', r'').replace(r'^', r'').replace(r':', r'').replace(r'#', r'').replace(r';', r'').replace(r'&', r'').replace(r'.', r'').replace(r'?', r'').replace(r'!', r'')
5481  return _obj

5492 def fval(_dict: dict, _search) -> str:
5493  """Search a dictionary by value and stop on first instance
5494 
5495  This searches key values that are tuples, lists, or strings.
5496  Returns the key (if found); else returns empty string
5497  """
5498  for key, val in _dict.items():
5499  if isinstance(val, str) and val == _search:
5500  return key
5501  elif _search in val:
5502  return key
5503  return ''

5506 def fvalhtml(_search: str, _type: str) -> str:
5507  """Search a dict by value to find the paired value; Stop on first instance
5508 
5509  For example, this finds '&#38;' or '&amp;' and returns the other value
5510  Returns HTML entity if found; else return empty string
5511  """
5512  _tuples = CODES.values()
5513  for v in _tuples:
5514  if not isinstance(v, (tuple, list)) or _search not in v:
5515  continue
5516  elif len(v) < 2 or len(v) > 4:
5517  continue
5518  if v[0] != _search:
5519  if (_type is 'name' and '#' not in v[0]) or (_type is 'num' and '&#' in v[0]):
5520  return v[0]
5521  elif v[1] != _search:
5522  if (_type is 'name' and '#' not in v[1]) or (_type is 'num' and '&#' in v[1]):
5523  return v[1]
5524  elif len(v) is 3 and v[2] != _search:
5525  if (_type is 'name' and '#' not in v[2]) or (_type is 'num' and '&#' in v[2]):
5526  return v[2]
5527  elif len(v) is 4 and v[3] != _search:
5528  if (_type is 'name' and '#' not in v[3]) or (_type is 'num' and '&#' in v[3]):
5529  return v[3]
5530  return r''

5533 def noescape(_hex: str) -> str:
5534  """Remove escapes from a single character hex string (\\U00000026, \\u0026, \\x26)"""
5535  if '\\U' in _hex and len(_hex) is 10:
5536  _int = int(_hex.replace('\\U', r''), 16)
5537  _hex = hex(_int).replace('0x', r'')
5538  return eval('"\\U{0}"'.format(_hex[:].zfill(8)))
5539  elif '\\u' in _hex and len(_hex) is 6:
5540  _int = int(_hex.replace('\\u', r''), 16)
5541  _hex = hex(_int).replace('0x', r'')
5542  return eval('"\\u{0}"'.format(_hex[:].zfill(4)))
5543  elif '\\x' in _hex and (len(_hex) % 4) is 0:
5544  _utf8_strict = '.decode(\'utf8\', \'strict\')'
5545  if _hex.count('\\x') is 4:
5546  _hex = _hex.split('\\x')[1:]
5547  _eval_str = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\\x{0[2]}\\x{0[3]}\'' + _utf8_strict
5548  return eval(_eval_str.format(_hex))
5549  elif _hex.count('\\x') is 3:
5550  _hex = _hex.split('\\x')[1:]
5551  _eval_str = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\\x{0[2]}\'' + _utf8_strict
5552  return eval(_eval_str.format(_hex))
5553  elif _hex.count('\\x') is 2:
5554  _hex = _hex.split('\\x')[1:]
5555  _eval_str = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\'' + _utf8_strict
5556  return eval(_eval_str.format(_hex))
5557  elif _hex.count('\\x') is 1:
5558  _int = int(_hex.replace('\\x', r''), 16)
5559  _hex = hex(_int).replace('0x', r'')[:].zfill(2)
5560  return eval('\'\\x{0}\''.format(_hex))
5561  else:
5562  raise Exception(r'Invalid input passed to noescape()!')
5563  elif isinstance(_hex, str) and len(_hex) is 1:
5564  return _hex
5565  else:
5566  raise Exception(r'Invalid input passed to noescape()!')

5572 def isascii(_str: str) -> bool:
5573  """Test if a character is within the Ascii limit
5574 
5575  >>> isascii('B')
5576  True
5577  >>> isascii('b')
5578  True
5579  >>> isascii('1')
5580  True
5581  >>> isascii('€')
5582  False
5583  >>> isascii('ἀ')
5584  False
5585  >>> isascii('€')
5586  False
5587  """
5588  try:
5589  return 0 <= ord(_str) < UPPER_LIMIT_ASCII_EXT
5590  except SyntaxError:
5591  return False

5610  False

5842 def isunicode(_str: str) -> bool: # flake8: noqa
5843  """Test if a string is within the Unicode limit"""
5844  assert isinstance(_str, (str, bytes)), \
5845  'An invalid datatype was passed to isunicode()!'
5846  _utfstrict = '.decode(\'utf8\', \'strict\')'
5847  _fmt = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\\x{0[2]}\'' + _utfstrict
5848  if len(_str) is 10 and '\\U' in _str:
5849  _int = int(_str.replace('\\U', ''), 16)
5850  return _int <= UPPER_LIMIT_UNICODE
5851  elif len(_str) is 6 and '\\u' in _str:
5852  _int = int(_str.replace('\\u', ''), 16)
5853  return _int <= UPPER_LIMIT_UNICODE
5854  elif _str.count('\\x') is 1 and (len(_str) % 4) is 0:
5855  _int = int(_str.replace('\\x', '0x'), 16)
5856  return _int <= UPPER_LIMIT_UNICODE
5857  elif _str.count('\\x') >= 2 and (len(_str) % 4) is 0:
5858  try:
5859  eval(_fmt.format(_str.split('\\x')[1:]))
5860  except SyntaxError:
5861  return False
5862  return True
5863  elif isinstance(_str, bytes):
5864  try:
5865  _str.decode('utf8', 'strict')
5866  except SyntaxError:
5867  return False
5868  return True
5869  elif len(_str) is 1:
5870  try:
5871  if len(_str.encode('utf-16', 'strict')):
5872  return True
5873  except SyntaxError:
5874  return False
5875  return False

5878 def hashexescape(_str: str) -> bool: # flake8: noqa
5879  """Test if the string contains a character hex escape"""
5880  if '\\U' in _str:
5881  _ct = _str.count('\\U')
5882  _start = 0
5883  while _ct != 0:
5884  _start = _str.find('\\U', _start) + 2
5885  _end = _start + 8
5886  _skip = False
5887  for i in _str[_start:_end]:
5888  if i in '0123456789ABCDEFabcdef':
5889  continue
5890  _skip = True
5891  break
5892  if not _skip:
5893  return True
5894  _ct -= 1
5895  _start = _end
5896  if '\\u' in _str:
5897  _ct = _str.count('\\u')
5898  _start = 0
5899  while _ct != 0:
5900  _start = _str.find('\\u', _start) + 2
5901  _end = _start + 4
5902  _skip = False
5903  for i in _str[_start:_end]:
5904  if i in '0123456789ABCDEFabcdef':
5905  continue
5906  _skip = True
5907  break
5908  if not _skip:
5909  return True
5910  _ct -= 1
5911  _start = _end
5912  if '\\X' in _str:
5913  _ct = _str.count('\\X')
5914  _start = 0
5915  while _ct != 0:
5916  _start = _str.find('\\X', _start) + 2
5917  _end = _start + 2
5918  _skip = False
5919  for i in _str[_start:_end]:
5920  if i in '0123456789ABCDEFabcdef':
5921  continue
5922  _skip = True
5923  break
5924  if not _skip:
5925  return True
5926  _ct -= 1
5927  _start = _end
5928  if '\\x' in _str:
5929  _ct = _str.count('\\x')
5930  _start = 0
5931  while _ct != 0:
5932  _start = _str.find('\\x', _start) + 2
5933  _end = _start + 2
5934  _skip = False
5935  for i in _str[_start:_end]:
5936  if i in '0123456789ABCDEFabcdef':
5937  continue
5938  _skip = True
5939  break
5940  if not _skip:
5941  return True
5942  _ct -= 1
5943  _start = _end
5944  return False

5955 """
5956 Each byte in a UTF-8 byte-sequence consists of two parts -
5957  - marker bits (the most significant bits) - sequence of zero to four 1 bits followed by a 0
5958  - payload bits - x being payload bits
5959 
5960 
5961  - U-00000000 ... U-0000007F 0xxxxxxx
5962  - U-00000080 ... U-000007FF 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
5963  - U-00000800 ... U-0000FFFF 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
5964  - U-00010000 ... U-0010FFFF 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
5965 """
5966

6061 def findescapes(_str: str) -> list:
6062  r"""Find character hex escapes in a string
6063

6071  def _search(_char: str, _num: int):
6072  """Find hex characters"""
6073  _ct = _str.count(_char)
6074  _start = 0
6075  while _ct != 0:
6076  _start = _str.find(_char, _start) + 2
6077  _end = _start + _num
6078  _skip = False
6079  for i in _str[_start:_end]:
6080  if i in r'0123456789ABCDEFabcdef':
6081  continue
6082  _skip = True
6083  break
6084  _ct -= 1
6085  if _skip:
6086  _start = _end
6087  continue
6088  _out.append(_char + _str[_start:_end])
6089  _start = _end
6090  return _out
6091 
6092  _out = []
6093  if '\\U' in _str:
6094  _out.append(_search('\\U', 8))
6095  if '\\u' in _str:
6096  _out.append(_search('\\u', 4))
6097  if '\\x' in _str:
6098  _out.append(_search('\\x', 2))
6099  if '\\X' in _str:
6100  _out.append(_search('\\X', 2))
6101  return _out

6111  _data = _data.replace(i, refnum2char(i))
6112  for i in re.findall(ENTITY_REF, _data):
6113  _data = _data.replace(i, refname2char(i))
6114  return _data

6117 def htmlescape(_str: str, quote: bool=True):
6118  """Replace special characters "&", "<", and ">" to HTML-escapes
6119 
6120  If the optional flag quote is true (default), double quote (") and
6121  single quote (') characters are also escaped.
6122 
6123  >>> htmlescape('This <b>is</b> a "test" (&).')
6124  'This &lt;b&gt;is&lt;/b&gt; a &quot;test&quot; (&amp;).'
6125  >>> htmlescape('This <b>is</b> a "test" (&).', False)
6126  'This &lt;b&gt;is&lt;/b&gt; a "test" (&amp;).'
6127  """
6128  _str = _str.replace(r'&', r'&amp;').replace(r'<', r'&lt;').replace(r'>', r'&gt;')
6129  if quote:
6130  _str = _str.replace('"', r'&quot;').replace('\'', r'&#39;')
6131  return _str

6134 def htmlunescape(_str: str):
6135  """Unescape &, ', ", <, and >
6136 
6137  >>> htmlunescape('This &#x3c;b&#62;is&lt;/b&gt; a &#34;test&quot; (&amp;).')
6138  'This <b>is</b> a "test" (&).'

6140  'This <b>is</b> a "test" (&).'
6141  """
6142  if '&' not in _str:
6143  return _str
6144  _str = _str.replace(r'&#x27;', r'\'').replace(r'&#39;', r'\'').replace(r'&apos;', r'\'')
6145  _str = _str.replace(r'&#x22;', '"').replace(r'&#34;', '"').replace(r'&quot;', '"')
6146  _str = _str.replace(r'&#x3c;', r'<').replace(r'&#60;', r'<').replace(r'&lt;', r'<')
6147  _str = _str.replace(r'&#x3e;', r'>').replace(r'&#62;', r'>').replace(r'&gt;', r'>')
6148  _str = _str.replace(r'&x26;', r'&').replace(r'&#38;', r'&').replace(r'&amp;', r'&')

6152 def noescutf8hex(_hex: str) -> str:
6153  r"""Remove escapes from UTF-8 hex strings (\\x26)
6154 
6155  >>> noescutf8hex('\\x26')
6156  '&'
6157  """
6158  if '\\x' in _hex and (len(_hex) % 4) is 0:
6159  _utf8_strict = '.decode(\'utf8\', \'strict\')'
6160  if _hex.count('\\') == 3:
6161  _hex = _hex.split('\\x')[1:]
6162  _eval_str = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\\x{0[2]}\'' + _utf8_strict
6163  return eval(_eval_str.format(_hex))
6164  elif _hex.count('\\') == 2:
6165  _hex = _hex.split('\\x')[1:]
6166  _eval_str = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\'' + _utf8_strict
6167  return eval(_eval_str.format(_hex))
6168  elif _hex.count('\\') == 4:
6169  _hex = _hex.split('\\x')[1:]
6170  _eval_str = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\\x{0[2]}\\x{0[3]}\'' + _utf8_strict
6171  return eval(_eval_str.format(_hex))
6172  elif _hex.count('\\') == 1:
6173  _int = int(_hex.replace('\\x', ''), 16)
6174  _hex = hex(_int).replace('0x', '')[:].zfill(2)
6175  return eval('\'\\x{0}\''.format(_hex))
6176  if isinstance(_hex, str) and len(_hex) is 1:
6177  return _hex
6178  raise ValueError('Invalid input passed to noescutf8hex()!')

6222 def int2char(_int, _numbase: str='10', _escape: bool=True) -> str:
6223  """Convert an integer (as a str or int type) to a character
6224 
6225  The integer may be decimal, hex, octal, or binary
6226  By default, the returned value is escaped unicode (\\U0000000)
6227  int2char(_int, _numbase, _escape) => str
6228  _int - number to convert to a character
6229  _numbase - Specify the int's base (2, 8, 10, 16)
6230  _escape - False = No escapes; True = Escapes
6231  int2char(38) => \\U00000026
6232  int2char('38') => \\U00000026
6233  int2char('0x26') => \\U00000026
6234  int2char(0x26) => \\U00000026
6235  int2char('26', '16') => \\U00000026
6236  int2char('26', '16', False) => &
6237  """
6238  if isinstance(_int, str):
6239  if '0x' in _int or _numbase is '16' or _numbase is 'hex':
6240  _int = int(_int, 16)
6241  elif '0b' in _int or _numbase is '2' or _numbase is 'bin':
6242  _int = int(_int, 2)
6243  elif '0o' in _int or _numbase is '8' or _numbase is 'oct':
6244  _int = int(_int, 8)
6245  else:
6246  _int = int(_int, 10)
6247  if isinstance(_int, int):
6248  if _escape:
6249  _int = hex(_int).replace('0x', '')[:].zfill(8)
6250  return '\\U{0}'.format(_int)
6251  else:
6252  if LOWER_LIMIT_ASCII_CTRL <= _int <= UPPER_LIMIT_UTF8:
6253  return chr(_int)
6254  elif UPPER_LIMIT_UTF8 < _int <= UPPER_LIMIT_UNICODE:
6255  _int = hex(_int).replace('0x', '')
6256  return eval('"\\U{0}"'.format(_int[:].zfill(8)))
6257  raise ValueError(r'An out-of-range integer passed to int2char()!')
6258  raise TypeError(r'Invalid datatype passed to int2char()!')

6530 def refnum2refname(_refnum: str) -> str:
6531  """Convert Decimal-NCR/HTML-Entity (&#38;) to HTML entity name (&amp;)"""
6532  assert '&#' in _refnum and ';' in _refnum, \
6533  'The entered value is not a HTML entity number (&#38;)!'
6534  return fvalhtml(_refnum, 'name')

6543 
6544 
6545 def char2intstr(_char: str) -> int:
6546  """Convert a character(s) to decimal integers as a str"""
6547  if len(_char) is 1:
6548  return str(ord(_char))
6549  elif len(_char) > 1:
6550  _out = ''
6551  for i in _char:
6552  _out += str(ord(i))
6553  return _out
6554  raise ValueError(r'Invalid data input in char2intstr()!')

6557 def str2bytes(_str: str, _encoding: str='utf8') -> bytes:
6558  """Convert strings to bytes"""
6559  return _str.encode(_encoding, 'strict')
6560 
6561 
6562 def bytes2str(_bytes: bytes, _encoding: str='utf8') -> str:
6563  """Convert bytes to strings"""
6564  return _bytes.decode(_encoding, 'strict')
6565 
6566 
6567 def int2hexbytes(_int: int, _length: int=2, _endian: str='little', _signed: bool=False) -> str:
6568  """Convert int to bytes represented as an escaped hex string
6569  If byteorder is "big", the most significant byte is at the beginning of the byte array.
6570  If byteorder is "little", the most significant byte is at the end of the byte array.
6571  """
6572  return _int.to_bytes(_length, _endian, signed=_signed)

6576  """Convert a hex string to a bytearray"""
6577  return bytearray.fromhex(_hex)

6580 # BUBBLE TEXT
6581 
6582 
6583 def text2bubble(_str: str) -> str:
6584  """Convert a plain-text string to bubble text
6585 
6586  >>> text2bubble('This (str) is a sample test.')
6587  'Ⓣⓗⓘⓢ (⃝ ⓢⓣⓡ)⃝ ⓘⓢ ⓐ ⓢⓐⓜⓟⓛⓔ ⓣⓔⓢⓣ.⃝ '
6588  >>> text2bubble('Testing various characters: €, *, Ω, ᾲ, and ⛽.')
6589  'Ⓣⓔⓢⓣⓘⓝⓖ ⓥⓐⓡⓘⓞⓤⓢ ⓒⓗⓐⓡⓐⓒⓣⓔⓡⓢ:⃝ €⃝ ,⃝ *⃝ ,⃝ Ω⃝ ,⃝ ᾲ⃝ ,⃝ ⓐⓝⓓ ⛽⃝ .⃝ '
6590  """
6591  _out = ''
6592  for i in _str:
6593  if i not in PLAIN_TEXT:
6594  i = i + '\u20dd '
6595  _out = _out + i
6596  return _out.translate(TRANS_TAB_TEXT2BUBBLE)
6597 
6598 
6599 def bubble2text(_str: str) -> str:
6600  """Convert bubble text to a plain-text string
6601 
6602  >>> bubble2text('Ⓣⓗⓘⓢ ⓘⓢ ⓐ ⓣⓔⓢⓣ.⃝')
6603  'This is a test.'
6604  >>> bubble2text('Ⓣⓗⓘⓢ ⓘⓢ ⓐ ⓢⓔⓒⓞⓝⓓ (⃝ ②ⓝⓓ)⃝ ⓣⓔⓢⓣ.⃝ ')
6605  'This is a second (2nd) test.'
6606  >>> bubble2text('Ⓣⓔⓢⓣⓘⓝⓖ ⓥⓐⓡⓘⓞⓤⓢ ⓒⓗⓐⓡⓐⓒⓣⓔⓡⓢ:⃝ €⃝ ,⃝ *⃝ ,⃝ Ω⃝ ,⃝ ᾲ⃝ ,⃝ ⓐⓝⓓ ⛽⃝ .⃝ ')
6607  'Testing various characters: €, *, Ω, ᾲ, and ⛽.'
6608  """
6609  _str = _str.replace('\u202f', r'').replace('\\u202f', r'')
6610  return _str.translate(TRANS_TAB_BUBBLE2TEST).replace('\u20dd ', r'').replace('\u20dd', r'')

6615 
6616 def text2square(_str: str, square_spaces: bool=False) -> str:
6617  """Convert a plain-text string to square text
6618 
6619  >>> text2square('This (str) is a sample test.', True)
6620  'T⃞ h⃞ i⃞ s⃞ ⃞ (⃞ s⃞ t⃞ r⃞ )⃞ ⃞ i⃞ s⃞ ⃞ a⃞ ⃞ s⃞ a⃞ m⃞ p⃞ l⃞ e⃞ ⃞ t⃞ e⃞ s⃞ t⃞ .⃞ '
6621  >>> text2square('This (str) is a sample test.')
6622  'T⃞ h⃞ i⃞ s⃞ (⃞ s⃞ t⃞ r⃞ )⃞ i⃞ s⃞ a⃞ s⃞ a⃞ m⃞ p⃞ l⃞ e⃞ t⃞ e⃞ s⃞ t⃞ .⃞ '
6623  >>> text2square('Testing various characters: €, *, Ω, ᾲ, and ⛽.')
6624  'T⃞ e⃞ s⃞ t⃞ i⃞ n⃞ g⃞ v⃞ a⃞ r⃞ i⃞ o⃞ u⃞ s⃞ c⃞ h⃞ a⃞ r⃞ a⃞ c⃞ t⃞ e⃞ r⃞ s⃞ :⃞ €⃞ ,⃞ *⃞ ,⃞ Ω⃞ ,⃞ ᾲ⃞ ,⃞ a⃞ n⃞ d⃞ ⛽⃞ .⃞ '
6625  """
6626  _out = ''
6627  for i in _str:
6628  _out = _out + i + '\u20de '
6629  if not square_spaces:
6630  return _out.replace(' \u20de', r' ')
6631  return _out
